Wash and dry produce.

Trim @mini cucumber{1} and halve lengthwise; cut into thin wedges. Quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice @scallions{2}.

In a #small bowl{}, toss cucumber with juice from one lemon wedge, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @apricot jam{1}, @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @spinach{5%ounce}, @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, and scallions; toss to coat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{90%seconds}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Place cucumber on the bottom two-thirds of each tortilla and top with as much spinach salad as you like. Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates and serve with any remaining spinach salad on the side.